sd=Credit Facility	Maintain the availability and allocation of a negotiated credit line or facility for a corporate customer, including supporting subsidiary allocations where appropriate	Example of use:A corporate customer obtains a credit facility after an equity financing round in order to better structure its debt in its capital structure	The credit facility provides a corporate with a flexible umbrella loan arrangement that can be drawn on over the term of the facility. It can be set up as a term, revolving, committed, letters of credit or most retail credit types of loan. It is typically collateralized and the rates, repayment structure and fees are defined for the term of the facility depending on the customer's past repayment performance and other considerations
sdpath=credit-facility
crpath=credit-facility-fulfillment-arrangement
crr=Credit Facility Fulfillment Arrangement Instance
mcr=Credit Facility Fulfillment Arrangement
bqs=Interest ServiceFees Maintenance Repayment Restructuring
CONFIG
CreditFacilityFulfillmentArrangement	initiate	Initiate a credit facility		initiateCreditFacilityFulfillmentArrangement		#desc
CreditFacilityFulfillmentArrangement	update	Update details for an existing credit facility		updateCreditFacilityFulfillmentArrangement		#desc
CreditFacilityFulfillmentArrangement	control	Control a credit facility arrangement (e.g. suspend, terminate)		controlCreditFacilityFulfillmentArrangement		#desc
